<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>FAQs</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.0.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <link href="/css/homepage.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jquery@3.6.0/dist/jquery.slim.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/popper.js@1.16.1/dist/umd/popper.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@4.6.1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">
  <%- include("#homeheader.ejs"); %>
  <%- include("#homenavbar.ejs"); %>
    <br><br>
    <h5 style="text-align: center; color: rgb(54, 54, 165)">Frequently Asked Questions</h5>
    <br>
    <div id="accordion" style="font-size: 14px;">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <a class="card-link" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseOne" style="color: rgb(54, 54, 165);">
                <strong>Question: </strong>Can givers claim money while giving things to the takers?
            </a>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" data-parent="#accordion">
            <div class="card-body">
              <strong>Answer: </strong>No. The purpose of this web application is to reuse things. So givers can not claim any money to the takers while giving something.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <a class="collapsed card-link" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseTwo" style="color: rgb(54, 54, 165);">
              <strong>Question: </strong>What are the things can be donated?
            </a>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion">
            <div class="card-body">
              <strong>Answer: </strong>Any household item that you are not going to use again, you can donate to others using this web application. It is very important for givers to select the category and subcategory of the item while raising pickup request so that takers can search their required item efficiently.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-header">
            <a class="collapsed card-link" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseThree" style="color: rgb(54, 54, 165);">
              <strong>Question: </strong>Can givers donate many items in one single pickup requests?.
            </a>
          </div>
          <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion">
            <div class="card-body">
              <strong>Answer: </strong>Yes, givers can donate many things in one single pickup requests. However, it is recommended to raise seperate pickup request for each item so that things are shared with many receivers to fullfil their requirements. 
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </div>    

    <%- include("#homefooter.ejs"); %>
</div>

</body>
</html>